Class Try.Companion

  • net.corda.core.utilities.Try.Companion
  • Enclosing class:
    Try<A>

    public static class Try.Companion

    • Method Detail

      • on

        @JvmStatic
 @NotNull
public <T> Try<T> on(@NotNull
                                          kotlin.jvm.functions.Function0<? extends T> body)

        Executes the given block of code and returns a class Try.Success capturing the result, or a class Try.Failure if a Throwable is thrown.

        It is recommended this be chained with throwError to ensure critial Errors are thrown and not captured.

        See Also:
        class Try.Success, class Try.Failure, Throwable, throwError, Error
